I don't know about you, but I prefer to have my text as original as
possible, and do my own editing, rather than rely on someone else.
one inexcusable example is what editors do to Mercutio's 'Queene Mab'
speech. Compare the Folio version with any of the edited versions. All
the ones I've seen take a speech that is mostly in prose, and change
it to complete verse. Of course this requires substitution of words,
and drastic changes of punctuation. They all take out from &quot;the lash
of Philome&quot;, making it in several versions, &quot;the lash of film&quot;. Look
up Philome sometime, and you might be very surprised.
